Introduction

Heo Young Ji is a South Korean Rapper, Dancer, Singer, Actress, and Variety Star under SM Culture & Contents. She is best known for being the Main Rapper, Lead Dancer, Vocalist, and Maknae of the girl group KARA under RBW.

She was added to KARA through the survival show KARA Project in 2014. Following the group's disbandment in 2016, Youngji continued to appear on dramas and variety shows.

Youngji made her debut as a solo artist on September 12th, 2023, with the single 'Toi Toi Toi'.

On September 5, 2024, Youngji announced through Instagram that she left DSP Media after 10 years.
